In the Confluence editor's insert Macro function, can we sort macros within the macro browser via both alphabetically & popularity and default to popularity to try to expose the best macros to people by default?

This is raised by [~pcurren] on behalf of [~grahan01] from [this comment|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Confluence+4+Editor+-+Customer+Feedback?focusedCommentId=296092039#comment-296092039].

See the attached video. To summarise create the following structure in Chrome -
{noformat}
<p>para 1</p>
<p>para 2<br>line 2 of para 2</p>
{noformat}

Then try and backspace from the start of "para 2".

The result is this structure -
{noformat}
<p>para 1para2</p>
<p>line 2 of para 2</p>
{noformat}

You would instead expect this -
{noformat}
<p>para 1para2<br>
line 2 of para 2</p>
{noformat}

Which is what you get in browsers other than Chrome/Safari.

